WEBVTT

00:00.024 --> 00:04.972
♪ Hey, why is it happening ♪

00:05.944 --> 00:08.652
♪ My heart is racing ♪

00:09.784 --> 00:13.792
♪ The world has fallen silent ♪

00:13.816 --> 00:18.572
♪ Hey, when I imagine you ♪

00:19.608 --> 00:22.636
♪ What kind of look ♪

00:23.640 --> 00:27.584
♪ Attracted me to you ♪

00:27.608 --> 00:30.880
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

00:30.904 --> 00:34.368
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

00:34.392 --> 00:39.640
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

00:39.640 --> 00:41.258
♪ I love you ♪

00:41.258 --> 00:44.736
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

00:44.760 --> 00:48.032
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

00:48.056 --> 00:53.728
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

00:53.752 --> 00:55.096
♪ I love you ♪

00:55.096 --> 00:58.432
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

00:58.456 --> 01:01.804
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

01:01.912 --> 01:07.109
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

01:07.109 --> 01:08.792
♪ I love you ♪

01:08.792 --> 01:12.192
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

01:12.216 --> 01:15.616
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

01:15.640 --> 01:21.216
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

01:21.240 --> 01:24.652
♪ I love you ♪

01:26.930 --> 01:27.720
=Love Me, Love My Voice=

01:27.720 --> 01:30.716
=Love Me, Love My Voice=
=Episode 26=

01:31.272 --> 01:34.460
(You are not just Mo Qingcheng to me.)

01:35.068 --> 01:38.805
Hello, I'm Guai,
from Zhaozhaomumu Music Studio.

01:38.829 --> 01:43.128
I'm the club leader,
and that's my name online.

01:44.669 --> 01:50.368
We'll perform "Peach-Blossom Springs"
composed and arranged by Shengshengman.

01:52.909 --> 01:57.604
Zhaozhaomumu sounds familiar.
Golden Piglet is from that club.

01:57.628 --> 01:58.969
Really?

02:01.469 --> 02:05.084
I mentioned Shengshengman
because the rules said

02:05.108 --> 02:08.924
that we should clarify the composer
and arranger of the song.

02:08.948 --> 02:13.405
Don't worry.
We're not going to favor anybody.

02:13.429 --> 02:17.448
We have members from many clubs.
It's a fair competition.

02:17.749 --> 02:20.885
Yeah, take it easy.
I also chose Shengshengman's song.

02:20.909 --> 02:23.328
She's productive. It's okay.

02:24.869 --> 02:27.489
Yeah, let's get started.

02:50.728 --> 02:52.608
This is not bad.

03:18.668 --> 03:20.369
You know the song?

03:22.228 --> 03:23.328
Of course.

03:24.068 --> 03:26.684
- Look how proud you are.
- You're jealous?

03:27.240 --> 03:28.769
I dare not.

03:40.309 --> 03:41.769
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

03:44.309 --> 03:46.128
- Let me.
- Let me.

03:49.429 --> 03:51.764
Hello, I'm the second contestant.

03:51.788 --> 03:55.084
I don't belong to any club.
I'm Half a Bottle of Yogurt.

03:55.108 --> 03:59.929
I'm also playing "Peach-Blossom Springs"
by Shengshengman.

04:00.909 --> 04:02.484
Again, your song.

04:02.508 --> 04:04.964
Excuse me, one suggestion.

04:04.988 --> 04:09.685
They just performed this song
and we liked it.

04:09.709 --> 04:12.329
Did you prepare another song?

04:13.469 --> 04:15.452
This is my...

04:15.816 --> 04:18.485
This is my first work online.

04:18.509 --> 04:21.608
It means a lot to me.

04:22.376 --> 04:25.129
Alright, we respect that.

04:25.348 --> 04:26.449
Thank you.

04:26.909 --> 04:28.248
(Proud of you.)

04:36.126 --> 04:38.463
(Proud of you.)

05:04.469 --> 05:06.269
- You were amazing.
- Really?

05:06.269 --> 05:07.608
See you around.

05:08.108 --> 05:09.288
Mr. Mo.

05:09.709 --> 05:11.168
- Mr. Mo.
- Mr. Mo.

05:12.308 --> 05:14.569
I'm not a judge. Don't be nervous.

05:15.829 --> 05:19.548
Since you're here,
let me treat you to some snacks.

05:19.829 --> 05:21.969
What about us?

05:22.548 --> 05:24.728
You have work to do.

05:26.348 --> 05:27.624
Leave the things here.

05:27.624 --> 05:29.404
- Thank you, Mr. Mo.
- Thank you, Mr. Mo.

05:29.428 --> 05:31.084
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

05:31.108 --> 05:32.485
- Bye.
- Go ahead.

05:32.509 --> 05:33.724
- Bye.
- Bye.

05:33.748 --> 05:34.769
Enjoy.

05:37.509 --> 05:38.649
Here.

05:41.788 --> 05:45.048
I found this place by chance.
They have nice food.

05:53.389 --> 05:56.805
Sorry, we're fully booked.
Do you have a reservation?

05:56.829 --> 05:58.844
Yes, for 2 PM. Mr. Mo.

05:58.868 --> 06:02.005
Nice to see you, Mr. Mo.
Upstairs, please.

06:02.029 --> 06:03.048
Thank you.

06:05.228 --> 06:06.228
This way.

06:07.308 --> 06:08.308
Hurry up.

06:09.389 --> 06:10.449
This way.

06:15.788 --> 06:17.449
- Mr. Mo.
- Alright.

06:18.029 --> 06:19.089
Here.

06:19.428 --> 06:20.569
Take a seat.

06:25.269 --> 06:28.445
The afternoon tea is a set.
But we change the menu every day.

06:28.469 --> 06:31.644
Please choose a tea.
I'll prepare the desserts.

06:31.668 --> 06:33.569
- Okay, thank you.
- Thank you.

06:35.629 --> 06:38.769
- When did you book it?
- Before you came.

06:39.868 --> 06:41.404
How do you know we're coming?

06:41.428 --> 06:44.329
I checked the contestants with Off Key.

06:44.629 --> 06:46.449
Here, take a look.

06:47.069 --> 06:48.069
Okay.

06:53.269 --> 06:54.928
Which one is good?

06:57.829 --> 07:01.048
It's our first time here.
Any recommendations?

07:01.469 --> 07:04.860
I've only been here once.
Just pick whatever you like.

07:05.384 --> 07:06.728
Okay.

07:08.029 --> 07:09.329
What would you like?

07:10.188 --> 07:12.428
This one, maybe.

07:12.428 --> 07:13.573
(Chamomile Tea)

07:15.149 --> 07:18.688
These look fine,
but I don't know if they're good.

07:19.509 --> 07:23.089
It's okay. Go ahead.
I'll have them if you don't like them.

07:24.228 --> 07:26.209
(Antique Garden Tea)
I'll take this.

07:26.709 --> 07:28.488
- This one.
- Okay.

07:31.949 --> 07:34.069
- This one.
- This one.

07:34.069 --> 07:35.209
Okay.

07:36.069 --> 07:37.649
Sorry about that.

07:38.829 --> 07:40.009
Okay.

07:40.108 --> 07:41.129
Hello.

07:43.668 --> 07:48.529
- So sweet.
- So jealous.

07:52.709 --> 07:54.248
Alright, I got it.

07:57.108 --> 07:58.608
Good news.

07:59.389 --> 08:00.649
You rank first

08:01.469 --> 08:03.009
among Group One.

08:06.469 --> 08:07.728
Great!

08:08.509 --> 08:09.788
It's on me.

08:10.348 --> 08:13.409
Nobody favored you. It's totally fair.

08:16.829 --> 08:20.928
Linglong picked your song and wanted
to discuss the arrangement with you.

08:24.188 --> 08:26.164
You haven't picked an artist.

08:26.188 --> 08:28.485
But someone thinks highly of you
and wants to meet you.

08:28.509 --> 08:31.889
Do you have a minute?
Let's go back once Group Four finishes.

08:32.068 --> 08:34.168
Of course, anytime.

08:35.588 --> 08:38.205
Fine, but they can't snatch her from us.

08:38.229 --> 08:41.644
Of course not. I belong to Zhaozhaomumu.

08:41.668 --> 08:42.968
You'd better be.

08:47.188 --> 08:49.769
- Yeah.
- Mr. Mo, you are back.

08:50.428 --> 08:53.208
Guai, here they are.

08:54.668 --> 08:56.605
Hello, I'm Beidou Xiaoxing.

08:56.629 --> 09:00.485
I know, you must be Jianjian.
I've been following you for long.

09:00.509 --> 09:03.245
Then be my accompaniment at the concert.

09:03.269 --> 09:04.719
What are you talking about?

09:04.719 --> 09:07.968
We said we'd let her choose.
It's a fair competition.

09:08.029 --> 09:10.164
But the contest hasn't ended.

09:10.188 --> 09:13.485
We can pick someone we want.
I'm picking you.

09:13.509 --> 09:14.764
Me too.

09:14.788 --> 09:17.180
- They're fighting for her.
- They're fighting for her.

09:17.629 --> 09:21.365
Come on, Jianjian, you've been
taking my songs ever since our debut.

09:21.389 --> 09:22.924
Now you're taking my accompaniment.

09:22.948 --> 09:25.564
What? It's a fair competition.

09:25.588 --> 09:28.489
We're girls. Girls help girls.

09:28.788 --> 09:32.485
Come on, Wang Ke, Feishao.
Say something. How's that fair?

09:32.509 --> 09:34.885
- We think...
- It's hard to say.

09:34.909 --> 09:38.468
- It's not so ideal.
- What do you mean?

09:38.468 --> 09:41.005
How about this?
Both of you sing for us now.

09:41.029 --> 09:44.125
Let Guai decide
who she wants to work with.

09:44.149 --> 09:46.548
- Sounds cool.
- Sounds cool.

09:46.548 --> 09:47.989
- Here we go.
- Here we go.

09:47.989 --> 09:51.568
- Here we go.
- Here we go.

09:51.749 --> 09:54.769
- No problem.
- Go ahead.

09:55.029 --> 09:58.245
- Sing for us.
- Sing for us.

09:58.269 --> 10:00.729
- I'm going to sing.
- Yeah.

10:01.548 --> 10:03.729
- Hurry up.
- I'm going to sing.

10:03.869 --> 10:08.044
No need, I'm a big fan. I've listened
to their songs a million times.

10:08.068 --> 10:10.029
- It's alright.
- He's ready.

10:10.029 --> 10:12.229
- Live is different.
- Totally.

10:12.229 --> 10:13.284
- Totally.
- Yeah.

10:13.308 --> 10:15.088
Leader, what do I do?

10:17.308 --> 10:20.288
Yeah, you're the club leader. Come on.

10:20.468 --> 10:21.269
- Let go.
- Guai.

10:21.269 --> 10:25.928
- We need to talk.
- Let go.

10:26.708 --> 10:28.288
Don't run away.

10:29.389 --> 10:31.068
You still have to sing.

10:31.656 --> 10:34.409
May I talk to your girlfriend?

10:36.188 --> 10:37.448
Another one gone.

10:38.588 --> 10:41.788
- I listened to your new song.
- How about it?

10:42.344 --> 10:45.245
I don't have suggestions, but...

10:45.269 --> 10:50.125
Can I sing that
at the concert of traditional songs?

10:50.149 --> 10:53.409
Really? That's my honor.

10:58.029 --> 11:01.649
But I haven't come up with the lyrics.

11:08.308 --> 11:12.808
I think we can try something
like four-character poems.

11:13.188 --> 11:16.208
Four-character poems?

11:27.308 --> 11:32.804
I got it. I know who I should talk to.

11:32.828 --> 11:36.168
Sheng is such a nice girl.

11:37.468 --> 11:40.649
She's talented and low-key.

11:42.149 --> 11:43.208
Mr. Mo.

11:46.349 --> 11:48.524
- Come on, let's eat.
- Come on, sit.

11:48.548 --> 11:50.365
- Sit.
- Take a seat.

11:50.389 --> 11:52.029
- Dig in.
- Take a seat.

11:52.029 --> 11:53.169
There are many people today,

11:53.169 --> 11:54.828
- so we ordered many dishes. Dig in.
- Alright.

11:54.828 --> 11:56.644
Mr. Mo is working on the main dish.

11:56.668 --> 11:59.129
- Take a bite.
- You like this too?

11:59.349 --> 12:02.205
- Get up. Show some manners.
- What's wrong?

12:02.229 --> 12:03.609
Let them sit.

12:04.149 --> 12:06.349
- I didn't see them.
- Me neither. Sit.

12:06.349 --> 12:07.245
- No need.
- Come on.

12:07.269 --> 12:09.684
You're special. You're family.

12:09.708 --> 12:11.605
Eat and drink whatever you want.

12:11.629 --> 12:14.085
- Don't be shy.
- Thanks.

12:14.109 --> 12:16.524
- Here we go.
- Wait.

12:16.548 --> 12:19.909
- Here comes Golden Piglet.
- Thank you so much.

12:19.909 --> 12:20.885
- Thank you.
- Come on.

12:20.909 --> 12:23.308
- Help her.
- Fish. Mr. Mo makes perfect fish.

12:23.308 --> 12:24.729
Try it.

12:25.308 --> 12:28.485
Mr. Mo said there are two pots
of bamboo shoot soup later. Enjoy.

12:28.509 --> 12:30.245
- Alright.
- Alright.

12:30.269 --> 12:32.188
- Thank you, Mr. Mo.
- Thank you, Mr. Mo.

12:32.308 --> 12:35.005
- Bamboo shoot soup again?
- It's a famous dish.

12:35.029 --> 12:38.284
- It's a meaningful dish.
- Yeah.

12:38.308 --> 12:39.948
- What do you mean?
- There's a story?

12:39.948 --> 12:41.889
Come on, tell us.

12:42.749 --> 12:46.389
It brings us to the day they met.

12:46.389 --> 12:49.088
That's enough, dig in.

12:51.668 --> 12:54.088
- I didn't say anything.
- Nothing.

12:54.188 --> 12:56.769
- Try it.
- Dig in.

12:59.029 --> 13:01.168
Here, try it.

13:03.869 --> 13:05.088
Have some bamboo.

13:21.188 --> 13:22.928
You're the best chef.

13:23.468 --> 13:24.688
Try it.

13:31.989 --> 13:34.009
Let me get some bowls.

13:36.509 --> 13:39.448
But I'm not sure if it's enough.

14:02.349 --> 14:03.448
What's wrong?

14:07.548 --> 14:11.609
You don't get it. It's a mood swing.

14:17.588 --> 14:19.529
Mood swing?

14:29.948 --> 14:36.088
As a fan of Qiang Qingci,
I have a reason to have mood swings.

14:41.229 --> 14:44.688
When I see those senior dubbing actors,

14:45.349 --> 14:49.489
I remember the days
when this circle was founded.

14:50.428 --> 14:53.820
But you will step down from the stage.

14:54.376 --> 14:56.968
And it gets me upset.

15:02.068 --> 15:03.928
You're not just

15:04.909 --> 15:06.849
Mo Qingcheng to me.

15:07.788 --> 15:09.808
You're also Qiang Qingci.

15:14.749 --> 15:16.808
I fell for Qiang Qingci

15:17.349 --> 15:20.088
way earlier than I fell for you.

15:24.109 --> 15:29.328
I think I need to
do something about that account.

15:34.588 --> 15:37.369
- It smells amazing.
- It smells amazing.

15:38.869 --> 15:40.529
Sorry, bad timing.

15:41.588 --> 15:46.804
I wanted to bring it to you.
Have some since you're here.

15:46.828 --> 15:49.205
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

15:49.229 --> 15:51.668
- Here.
- I'll grab this one.

15:51.668 --> 15:53.849
- Alright.
- Here.

15:54.749 --> 15:57.164
I heard that your love story
started with this dish.

15:57.188 --> 16:00.048
So we rushed here to taste it.

16:03.149 --> 16:04.540
What would you like?

16:06.509 --> 16:08.448
Bamboo shoot soup?

16:10.788 --> 16:13.088
How does it taste? Is it to your liking?

16:13.909 --> 16:16.005
It's very tasty.

16:16.029 --> 16:20.164
- What's it called again?
- I forgot as well.

16:20.188 --> 16:21.424
I'm having amnesia.

16:21.448 --> 16:24.328
- What's it called?
- I don't remember.

16:24.389 --> 16:26.249
Bamboo shoot soup.

16:28.588 --> 16:30.924
- I'll remember it.
- Bamboo shoot soup.

16:30.948 --> 16:33.325
But it's not the perfect season.

16:33.349 --> 16:36.769
It's the best in winter.

16:37.468 --> 16:38.308
- Winter.
- Winter.

16:38.308 --> 16:40.804
- Winter.
- Winter.

16:40.828 --> 16:42.649
They started dating in the winter.

16:43.389 --> 16:47.328
- Got it. That's what it means.
- We interrupted them.

16:47.828 --> 16:51.968
- How many instruments can you play?
- How do we sleep here?

16:54.869 --> 16:57.885
Zhou Zheng,
have you checked the stadium?

16:57.909 --> 17:00.488
I need to confirm the quantity
and location of the posters.

17:01.149 --> 17:03.885
Yeah, I've checked it many times,
but it's hard to book

17:03.909 --> 17:05.565
because it's the busy season.

17:05.589 --> 17:09.208
But in the end,
I booked the place you like the most.

17:10.188 --> 17:12.569
Rest assured. I'll tell them.

17:13.069 --> 17:16.248
Hey, guys. Stop playing.
Are you staying here tonight?

17:17.028 --> 17:18.028
If you're staying...

17:18.028 --> 17:21.325
Feishao has a giant apartment.
Why do you have to stay here?

17:21.349 --> 17:24.244
Help me put some quilts on the floor
if you're staying here. Hurry up.

17:24.268 --> 17:25.968
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

17:26.188 --> 17:28.168
Why don't you come to my place?

17:28.948 --> 17:32.924
There are plenty of rooms.
And we can play golf in the morning.

17:32.948 --> 17:35.125
- Who plays golf?
- Let's do it.

17:35.149 --> 17:37.528
- Get it up there.
- See?

17:37.668 --> 17:40.700
- Nobody wants to visit except for me.
- Get lost.

17:41.428 --> 17:45.684
Ladies, it's too crowded here.
Want to crash at my place?

17:45.708 --> 17:48.565
No, thanks. I'm staying with my friend.

17:48.589 --> 17:51.204
- Okay.
- No, thanks. It's not convenient.

17:51.228 --> 17:52.964
My apartment is huge.

17:52.988 --> 17:56.188
First, you're a guy.
Secondly, I need to record tomorrow.

17:56.188 --> 17:59.988
I need a studio with instruments.
None are close to your place.

17:59.988 --> 18:01.164
- Let's invite them.
- Yeah.

18:01.188 --> 18:05.909
- I told you to move back to the city.
- Mind your own business.

18:05.909 --> 18:11.004
Why don't you come to our studio?
There's space and we have instruments.

18:11.028 --> 18:14.768
If I stay there,
will you be my accompaniment?

18:15.629 --> 18:18.805
Come on, Jianjian. You did that again?

18:18.829 --> 18:22.652
We said we'd let them think it over.
You're cheating here.

18:23.188 --> 18:25.109
- Go and stay there.
- I...

18:25.109 --> 18:27.049
I'm just seizing my chances.

18:27.389 --> 18:28.845
Thank you in advance.

18:28.869 --> 18:30.085
- No problem.
- Yeah.

18:30.109 --> 18:31.365
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

18:31.389 --> 18:33.004
- Let's go.
- Okay.

18:33.028 --> 18:36.805
- Want a ride?
- You can't drive all of them.

18:36.829 --> 18:38.704
I can drive you too.

18:38.728 --> 18:42.049
Okay, pack up. We'll get the cars.

18:43.112 --> 18:45.004
- Okay.
- See you.

18:45.028 --> 18:47.805
- Let me help you.
- Okay, thanks.

18:47.829 --> 18:49.809
- Bye.
- Bye.

18:53.508 --> 18:55.228
I got two beds from a salon.

18:55.228 --> 18:58.089
And we have the sofabed.
I think it's enough.

18:58.589 --> 19:02.125
Eryue and I will share the sofabed.
You can sleep separately.

19:02.149 --> 19:03.504
Is it too crowded?

19:03.528 --> 19:07.856
- Never mind. I'm going back.
- No, don't go.

19:07.880 --> 19:11.164
- We can talk like we're in college.
- Yeah.

19:11.188 --> 19:15.728
Stay, Guai. I can tell that
Jianjian wants to know more about you.

19:16.589 --> 19:21.285
I don't want you to be uncomfortable.
You've traveled a long way, after all.

19:21.309 --> 19:23.045
We don't mind it.

19:23.069 --> 19:26.525
We used to crash at our friend's place
when we were traveling for events.

19:26.549 --> 19:29.289
I know. I watched your interviews.

19:30.869 --> 19:34.644
I bought some toiletries
and toothbrushes.

19:34.668 --> 19:36.768
- Thanks, Golden Piglet.
- Thanks, Golden Piglet.

19:37.309 --> 19:39.928
Right, Sheng. Stay with us.

19:40.428 --> 19:43.109
Yeah, Sheng.
I didn't go to Yangshuo last time.

19:43.109 --> 19:45.609
We finally met. Stay with us.

19:45.869 --> 19:49.089
- But there's no space.
- Let's squeeze together.

19:49.188 --> 19:51.548
Share the sofa bed with us.

19:52.109 --> 19:53.436
Help us out.

19:53.992 --> 19:56.764
Stay here. I'll come
and make breakfast tomorrow.

19:57.268 --> 20:00.928
They keep saying that
they want to ask you for songs.

20:01.708 --> 20:06.728
- Alright, I'll stay.
- Awesome. Yeah.

20:07.389 --> 20:10.968
It's your club,
but I'm acting like the leader.

20:11.829 --> 20:12.968
It's okay.

20:13.349 --> 20:16.404
- Mr. Mo, I'll go back to Perfect Voice.
- Alright.

20:16.428 --> 20:17.885
- Bye.
- Bye.

20:17.909 --> 20:21.488
- Off Key, do you have a minute?
- What's wrong?

20:22.188 --> 20:25.404
Linglong chose my song for the concert.

20:25.428 --> 20:29.885
- Really? Congratulations.
- Wait, I'm not done.

20:29.909 --> 20:33.724
I haven't written the lyrics.
Are you interested?

20:33.748 --> 20:38.244
Me? Really? No problem.
I'll stay up all night for this.

20:38.268 --> 20:40.004
Alright, I'll send you the sheet.

20:40.028 --> 20:42.125
Do it now. I'm getting started.

20:42.149 --> 20:45.125
What's the rush?
I'll send it to you later.

20:45.149 --> 20:48.365
Alright, don't forget it. See you.

20:48.389 --> 20:50.204
- Alright, bye.
- Bye, Mr. Mo.

20:50.228 --> 20:51.409
Bye.

20:52.188 --> 20:55.244
Alright, that's about it.
I'm heading home.

20:55.268 --> 20:56.684
You can wait for the breakfast.

20:56.708 --> 20:59.244
- Okay, see you.
- See you tomorrow.

20:59.268 --> 21:03.248
I'll walk him out.

21:04.349 --> 21:05.369
Let's go.

21:05.789 --> 21:07.804
Don't take long, Sheng.

21:08.149 --> 21:10.728
Jianjian really likes Guai.

21:11.349 --> 21:13.809
Guai deserves it.

21:14.909 --> 21:18.569
Who do you think she's going to choose?
Beidou Xiaoxing or Jianjian?

21:18.708 --> 21:22.248
- I guess Jianjian.
- Me too.

21:22.948 --> 21:26.204
Alright, get back. I'll be here at 7 AM.

21:26.589 --> 21:28.809
Drive safe.

21:29.909 --> 21:32.049
I'll text you when I'm home.

21:32.948 --> 21:35.129
I'll wait for your message.

21:40.589 --> 21:42.008
Get back.

21:47.909 --> 21:50.889
- Drive safe.
- Okay.

21:55.069 --> 21:56.448
I'm back.

21:56.829 --> 22:00.528
- Sheng.
- What took you so long?

22:03.508 --> 22:09.168
Would you like some water?

22:09.508 --> 22:11.569
- Thanks, Golden Piglet.
- Thank you.

22:18.869 --> 22:20.208
- Morning.
- Morning.

22:21.549 --> 22:24.569
- Shush. They're still asleep.
- Okay.

22:27.228 --> 22:29.528
- Let me.
- It's okay. Let me.

22:32.629 --> 22:33.968
You slept on the sofa?

22:34.988 --> 22:37.409
Yeah, they are guests.

22:39.629 --> 22:41.089
Help me with breakfast.

22:46.109 --> 22:50.004
- They were praising you in the chat.
- About what?

22:50.028 --> 22:53.448
I heard you played
Peach-Blossom Springs yesterday.

22:54.349 --> 22:56.649
They wanted to hear it.

22:57.149 --> 22:58.524
They want you.

22:58.888 --> 23:02.409
I told them even we couldn't get you

23:03.109 --> 23:04.649
to The Perfect Voice Studio.

23:05.668 --> 23:09.688
I'm a composer.
I can't do much at Perfect Voice.

23:11.748 --> 23:15.569
You like this place
as much as I like Perfect Voice.

23:19.629 --> 23:23.085
- Food is ready.
- Breakfast is ready.

23:23.109 --> 23:24.208
Coming.

23:25.869 --> 23:28.204
- Sit.
- Breakfast made by Qiang Qingci.

23:28.228 --> 23:31.605
I've always been jealous of your staff.
Today is my day.

23:31.629 --> 23:34.609
Yeah, we'll get stuffed.

23:34.668 --> 23:37.404
Let me have some yogurt
to help with digestion.

23:37.428 --> 23:40.488
I wonder when we'll have
such an honor next time.

23:40.629 --> 23:42.204
- Dig in.
- I have an idea.

23:42.228 --> 23:45.204
Join Zhaozhaomumu. Sheng belongs here.

23:45.228 --> 23:49.829
Then you get to taste
these amazing dishes all the time.

23:49.829 --> 23:51.168
Exactly.

23:51.428 --> 23:54.484
- Want some chocolate cream?
- No, thanks.

23:54.508 --> 23:59.008
- Do you always make fun of Mr. Qiang?
- He's used to it.

23:59.468 --> 24:00.924
You know why?

24:00.948 --> 24:04.004
He always ignores us
when we make fun of him.

24:04.028 --> 24:04.924
Let me tell you.

24:04.948 --> 24:08.849
That makes you want to tease him more.

24:08.948 --> 24:10.569
You're rebellious.

24:10.988 --> 24:15.289
- Mr. Qiang, don't you mind it?
- I don't mind their little tricks.

24:15.668 --> 24:16.668
Thank you.

24:17.869 --> 24:20.488
Right, have you decided?

24:21.829 --> 24:24.244
Yeah, I'll be your accompaniment.

24:24.268 --> 24:27.329
Perfect. I will treat you right.

24:29.109 --> 24:32.849
- Sheng, I finished the lyrics.
- Really?

24:33.508 --> 24:35.125
- Hey, guys.
- Sit.

24:35.149 --> 24:36.369
- Morning.
- Sit.

24:37.748 --> 24:43.049
Your song matches perfectly
with Qi Yu in The Book of Songs.

24:58.149 --> 25:04.156
Behold by riverside,
green bamboos in high glee.

25:04.708 --> 25:06.528
- Sounds nice.
- Sounds nice.

25:06.869 --> 25:08.644
It's perfect.

25:08.668 --> 25:12.004
I always thought that
the melody was too slow for lyrics.

25:12.028 --> 25:15.085
But the poem added soul to this song.

25:15.109 --> 25:18.168
Really? That's the best reward
for a sleepless night.

25:18.748 --> 25:21.125
You stayed up all night for this?

25:21.149 --> 25:22.484
I was thrilled yesterday

25:22.508 --> 25:24.845
and kept thinking about
how to write the lyrics.

25:24.869 --> 25:27.684
- So I barely slept.
- Have some breakfast.

25:27.708 --> 25:31.968
- Here's a sandwich from Mr. Qiang.
- Thank you, Mr. Mo.

25:32.748 --> 25:34.008
Take a look.

25:35.268 --> 25:36.528
It's so good.

25:39.748 --> 25:46.556
Behold by riverside,
green bamboos in high glee.

25:48.228 --> 25:54.809
Our duke is dignified,
like polished ivory.

25:56.268 --> 25:57.768
- Who is it?
- Still asleep?

26:00.188 --> 26:01.208
Who is it?

26:03.549 --> 26:05.928
- It's you?
- Surprise.

26:06.668 --> 26:09.404
We need people for the ticket pre-sale.

26:09.428 --> 26:10.508
Come and help.

26:10.508 --> 26:12.805
What did I tell you? And they need us?

26:12.829 --> 26:14.045
Perfect timing.

26:14.069 --> 26:17.208
- You just woke up?
- Yeah, I just opened my eyes.

26:17.508 --> 26:19.248
You didn't bring anything?

26:19.909 --> 26:22.008
Look who's here.

26:23.988 --> 26:26.928
- Mu, Mo Bai.
- What's going on?

26:27.069 --> 26:29.409
- Come on.
- Come on.

26:29.549 --> 26:30.349
Xiaoxing.

26:30.349 --> 26:32.724
- It's been so long.
- It's been so long.

26:32.748 --> 26:34.668
- Give me a hug.
- Come on.

26:34.668 --> 26:37.684
- Give me a hug.
- It's been so long.

26:37.708 --> 26:39.369
- You look great.
- Kacey.

26:40.309 --> 26:42.228
- It's been so long.
- It's been years.

26:42.228 --> 26:43.684
- Right?
- Yeah.

26:43.708 --> 26:47.168
Only Qiang Qingci
has the charm to gather you here.

26:47.748 --> 26:51.644
- What about Wang Ke?
- Are you looking for trouble?

26:51.668 --> 26:53.589
- Yeah, let's eat.
- Come on.

26:53.589 --> 26:56.349
- Let's eat.
- Come for breakfast.

26:56.349 --> 26:57.809
Doudou.

27:09.948 --> 27:14.484
♪ Behold by riverside ♪

27:14.508 --> 27:18.644
♪ Bamboos so lush and green ♪

27:18.668 --> 27:21.188
♪ Our duke is dignified ♪

27:21.188 --> 27:23.188
♪ With gold-or tin-like sheen ♪

27:23.188 --> 27:26.484
♪ With his scepter in hand ♪

27:26.508 --> 27:31.045
♪ He is in gentle mood ♪

27:31.069 --> 27:34.968
♪ By his chariot he'd stand ♪

27:35.368 --> 27:38.244
♪ At jesting he is good ♪

27:38.268 --> 27:41.948
- ♪But he is never rude ♪
- Pause it.

27:43.948 --> 27:45.849
Have a rest and have some water.

27:56.428 --> 27:59.605
Leader, the key is too high.

27:59.629 --> 28:02.569
It's meant for Linglong. I can't.

28:02.629 --> 28:05.849
- Want to try it?
- Me?

28:06.428 --> 28:10.565
No way. I can't sing G minor.
I'm a mezzo-soprano.

28:10.589 --> 28:15.129
What do we do?
We said we'd send her the demo.

28:15.268 --> 28:18.248
Let's try with someone else.

28:22.789 --> 28:24.728
Let me check with my friend.

28:28.708 --> 28:30.008
I'll get the door.

28:32.309 --> 28:36.244
- Mr. Mo, why brought you here?
- Look who's here.

28:36.268 --> 28:37.924
- Come on in.
- Hello.

28:37.948 --> 28:39.569
Miss Linglong?

28:42.829 --> 28:45.164
Miss Linglong, what brought you here?

28:45.188 --> 28:49.404
I asked Mr. Mo to take me here.
I can't wait to hear the demo.

28:49.428 --> 28:51.569
Come on in. Take a seat.

28:55.268 --> 29:00.404
- Sorry about the mess. We just moved.
- It looks sweet and fun here.

29:00.428 --> 29:03.268
- Would you like to drink something?
- Hot water will do.

29:03.268 --> 29:03.885
Sit.

29:03.909 --> 29:06.609
- Mr. Mo, want to drink something?
- No, thanks.

29:07.428 --> 29:11.488
I heard that you used
a poem as the lyrics.

29:11.629 --> 29:16.285
That's his idea. Off Key. Lyric composer
of Zhaozhaomumu Music Studio.

29:16.309 --> 29:18.525
He stayed up all night for it.

29:18.549 --> 29:23.889
- I've seen you in Tianzi No. 1.
- I'm an employee at Perfect Voice.

29:25.668 --> 29:27.768
I'm also a member of Zhaozhaomumu.

29:28.789 --> 29:31.329
Will you show me the demo now?

29:36.389 --> 29:38.129
Miss Linglong.

29:38.188 --> 29:41.885
We wanted to record the demo
and send it to you.

29:41.909 --> 29:47.409
You wanted to? Is there a problem?

29:51.109 --> 29:55.724
The key is too high.
None of us can sing it.

29:55.748 --> 30:00.325
So we're looking for help.
We may send it to you tomorrow.

30:00.349 --> 30:02.168
Don't bother.

30:02.988 --> 30:04.728
I'm right here.

30:05.948 --> 30:09.049
You're recording the demo?

30:09.629 --> 30:11.724
But we just set up this place.

30:11.748 --> 30:14.045
- Everything's sloppy here.
- Yeah.

30:14.069 --> 30:17.845
The soul of a song lies in
the lyrics and melody.

30:17.869 --> 30:20.004
- Others don't matter.
- That's right.

30:20.028 --> 30:23.609
Why don't we just record the song today?

30:26.708 --> 30:28.728
You're doing it here?

30:30.789 --> 30:33.765
I have some ideas to contribute.

30:33.789 --> 30:37.164
I'd like to add a decorative tone
at the end of the first line

30:37.188 --> 30:39.924
to add to the traditional vibe.

30:39.948 --> 30:45.045
Something like "Behold by riverside".

30:45.069 --> 30:47.805
- Just a little bit.
- Got it. Sounds good.

30:47.829 --> 30:50.365
I have some ideas about the arrangement.

30:50.389 --> 30:54.125
For example, I'd like to add
a Chinese bass drum to the chorus.

30:54.149 --> 30:57.365
- It's going to sound majestic.
- Okay.

30:57.389 --> 31:01.164
- Let's do it.
- Okay.

31:01.188 --> 31:04.008
- Let me adjust the equipment for you.
- Okay.

31:13.789 --> 31:17.168
Miss Linglong, here we go.

31:18.268 --> 31:19.409
Okay.

31:35.880 --> 31:42.668
♪ Behold by riverside,
bamboos with soft green shade ♪

31:42.668 --> 31:44.649
Sounds amazing.

31:45.109 --> 31:51.085
♪ Our duke is dignified,
when crowned with strings of jade ♪

31:51.109 --> 31:55.900
♪ As bright as stars we find ♪

32:00.789 --> 32:04.609
♪ With solemn gravity ♪

32:37.909 --> 32:39.928
Amazing, Juemei.

32:40.428 --> 32:42.089
Nice place.

32:42.632 --> 32:47.369
We must present a perfect performance
to match this place found by Juemei.

32:48.228 --> 32:54.049
This is great.
Imagine if we turn on all the lights.

32:54.109 --> 32:58.188
Forget about the lights. They have
the best acoustic equipment in the city.

32:58.188 --> 32:59.409
Right?

32:59.869 --> 33:03.164
Perfect Voice deserves the best.

33:03.188 --> 33:04.768
Have you got the floor plan?

33:05.428 --> 33:08.525
- Mr. Mo.
- Mr. Qiang, I didn't know you'd come.

33:08.549 --> 33:10.849
I have to see the place.

33:11.708 --> 33:13.289
Floor plan.

33:15.228 --> 33:16.248
Is it fine?

33:17.468 --> 33:19.089
- Yeah.
- Right?

33:19.869 --> 33:21.089
The lights.

33:22.549 --> 33:25.109
It would be brilliant
for the stage effect.

33:25.109 --> 33:26.684
- Let me record this.
- Of course.

33:26.708 --> 33:28.248
- Zhou Zheng.
- Later...

33:28.389 --> 33:31.004
- How's the accommodation going?
- Almost done.

33:31.028 --> 33:33.204
Let's focus on the stage first, okay?

33:33.228 --> 33:36.684
What are you waiting for?
Mu, Mo Bai, come up here.

33:36.708 --> 33:39.525
- Stop taking photos.
- Stay further apart.

33:39.549 --> 33:41.869
- Okay, wait. Where's Off Key?
- Off Key.

33:41.869 --> 33:43.668
- Okay, let's finish your part.
- Okay.

33:43.668 --> 33:45.869
Hurry up. Come on stage.
What are you looking at?

33:45.869 --> 33:47.885
- Come on, Off Key.
- Coming.

33:47.909 --> 33:50.829
Just climb up here. Come on.

33:50.829 --> 33:53.468
- Coming.
- Only you can climb up. Be careful.

33:53.468 --> 33:58.568
- Hurry, Mu.
- Don't put your backpack there.

33:58.669 --> 34:01.325
- Hurry.
- Mo Bai.

34:01.349 --> 34:02.645
- Hurry.
- This is huge.

34:02.669 --> 34:05.769
Come up from here.

34:05.988 --> 34:08.604
- Off Key.
- Off Key. Come here.

34:08.628 --> 34:11.229
- You're the main figure.
- How do you like it?

34:11.229 --> 34:12.165
- Over there.
- Not bad.

34:12.189 --> 34:14.189
- Go closer.
- Here.

34:14.189 --> 34:17.404
Six people. Split up in half.

34:17.428 --> 34:21.765
Slightly tilted.
Four to five meters apart.

34:21.789 --> 34:25.404
- This place is better. Stay here.
- No problem. Better than his.

34:25.428 --> 34:29.088
Go find the red cloth. What's next?

34:30.389 --> 34:32.564
- What's next?
- General, no!

34:32.588 --> 34:35.004
- General, no!
- General, no!

34:35.028 --> 34:36.924
- Take over.
- Okay.

34:36.948 --> 34:41.044
- I have things to do.
- Go over there. Try it.

34:41.068 --> 34:42.369
What is the first line?

34:43.309 --> 34:44.404
- Again. Hurry.
- Yeah.

34:44.428 --> 34:47.084
- Again.
- That's his move.

34:47.108 --> 34:51.084
- I have things to do.
- Go ahead. I got this.

34:51.108 --> 34:55.269
We'll be in the center. Walk like this.

34:55.269 --> 34:56.628
- How do we do this?
- Yeah.

34:56.628 --> 34:57.789
- This way.
- This way.

34:57.789 --> 35:01.289
- And to the back.
- Yeah.

35:01.909 --> 35:03.968
It's closer like this.

35:06.108 --> 35:11.108
- Mu, how fast should you be?
- Run up stage.

35:11.108 --> 35:12.968
- Three, two, one.
- Don't sit there.

35:24.269 --> 35:27.028
Five seconds? Is it enough?
Time is really tight.

35:27.028 --> 35:30.645
They're both very emotional here.

35:30.669 --> 35:33.608
When you cue Zhao...

35:35.028 --> 35:40.805
This place will be full of people
with all kinds of IDs.

35:40.829 --> 35:45.249
They'll be strangers from
all walks of life and all ages.

35:45.829 --> 35:49.924
It's like the Spring Festival
we're celebrating

35:49.948 --> 35:52.088
with another type of family members.

35:52.588 --> 35:55.128
We must do our best for our family.

35:56.189 --> 35:57.249
You know?

35:57.309 --> 36:00.008
- Nervous?
- A little bit.

36:03.229 --> 36:04.568
What's Mr. Mo doing?

36:10.189 --> 36:12.829
Okay. Let's go. Rehearse the next part.

36:12.829 --> 36:13.964
- Okay.
- Don't be nervous.

36:13.988 --> 36:16.365
- Get going.
- Let's rehearse it.

36:16.389 --> 36:17.189
Get going.

36:17.189 --> 36:23.100
(First People's Hospital)

36:32.229 --> 36:33.229
Come in.

36:35.028 --> 36:37.608
- Have some water.
- Thanks.

36:38.189 --> 36:41.165
The stage design? Let me see.

36:41.189 --> 36:43.088
It happens to be your song.

36:43.428 --> 36:47.205
The green bamboo and river
in the background fit with the lyrics.

36:47.229 --> 36:48.249
Take a look.

36:48.869 --> 36:50.484
It's nice.

36:50.508 --> 36:55.568
With some dry ice and a follow spot,
it's going to be atmospheric.

36:56.749 --> 36:59.369
It's our first rehearsal. Will you come?

36:59.869 --> 37:02.169
Juemei is the director. He'll be there.

37:02.749 --> 37:06.205
I checked with Doudou.
I can attend the second rehearsal.

37:06.229 --> 37:08.849
Then we'll go on stage at night.

37:11.508 --> 37:13.568
Dr. Mo, someone is paging you.

37:16.148 --> 37:17.889
Cardiac Surgery.

37:19.108 --> 37:20.209
Go ahead.

37:25.749 --> 37:30.325
Xiyou, take the singers' costumes
to the stadium tomorrow morning.

37:30.349 --> 37:33.524
I'll wait for the suits
of the dubbing team.

37:33.548 --> 37:36.689
Okay, no problem. I got this.

37:37.068 --> 37:40.448
Doudou, these costumes are amazing.

37:41.468 --> 37:46.484
They paid for these.
Now I'm entrusting them to you.

37:46.508 --> 37:49.008
Rest assured,
I'll take good care of them.

37:51.468 --> 37:54.528
Doudou, Xiyou, look what we've got.

37:54.869 --> 37:56.524
- Hey.
- Look.

37:56.548 --> 37:58.488
- Get off.
- What are these?

37:59.988 --> 38:02.849
- Look.
- Good stuff. Port trotters.

38:02.909 --> 38:05.524
So many? Do they fit in the freezer?

38:05.548 --> 38:09.165
We'll cook them overnight
before the performance.

38:09.189 --> 38:12.205
- Bring it to the kitchen.
- Slowly.

38:12.229 --> 38:15.725
- Who bought this?
- The one who loves cooking.

38:15.749 --> 38:18.964
- He's going to cook?
- He's been working overtime.

38:18.988 --> 38:23.608
He said he wanted to do something
for everyone as the main producer.

38:23.829 --> 38:26.245
Yin got so excited and said

38:26.269 --> 38:30.004
that he should cook for all the staff.

38:30.028 --> 38:31.048
Let's go.

38:31.749 --> 38:35.289
- It's heavy.
- We'll get takeout and cook these.

38:35.869 --> 38:37.689
It's going to take all night.

38:41.749 --> 38:44.508
- It's not that heavy.
- Let me, Doudou.

38:44.508 --> 38:45.948
- It's okay.
- You got this?

38:45.948 --> 38:47.205
- Let me.
- You got this?

38:47.229 --> 38:48.528
You're strong.

38:48.869 --> 38:51.448
- It's nothing.
- Respect.

39:03.789 --> 39:05.209
(Nice moonlight.)

39:16.389 --> 39:18.249
I was worried you'd be late.

39:19.028 --> 39:22.849
Yeah, I had to do surgery
and didn't have time to tell you.

39:23.669 --> 39:26.689
- Got dry peppers?
- Over there.

39:33.428 --> 39:34.528
How many?

39:35.269 --> 39:39.128
- It's not enough. Is there more?
- So many?

39:39.349 --> 39:42.209
- Wait for me. I'll get more.
- Okay.

39:51.628 --> 39:54.608
- Are these enough?
- Yeah.

39:55.269 --> 39:57.568
Close the cashier, lock up,
and come to the studio.

40:06.309 --> 40:07.769
Mr. Mo, you're back.

40:09.309 --> 40:11.048
- Good evening.
- Hello.

40:11.269 --> 40:12.165
Hey, there.

40:12.189 --> 40:15.365
- Everything ready?
- Yeah, all in the kitchen.

40:15.389 --> 40:19.404
- I'm exhausted.
- I've never seen so many trotters.

40:19.428 --> 40:24.488
It never crossed my mind
you'd do this before the performance.

40:24.948 --> 40:27.928
Stop making fun of me.
Help me with the preparation.

40:28.229 --> 40:30.004
Alright, Xiyou. Go ahead. I'll help him.

40:30.028 --> 40:34.008
- Wake up. Go help.
- He was talking to you.

40:34.628 --> 40:36.845
- I'm not going. You do it.
- We're busy.

40:36.869 --> 40:38.769
- I got work.
- Me too.

40:38.909 --> 40:41.245
Zhou Zheng, hurry up.
The singers have work.

40:41.269 --> 40:43.845
- Look, Doudou is calling you.
- See?

40:43.869 --> 40:47.209
- How many staff are there?
- 136.

40:47.548 --> 40:50.769
If everyone gets two trotters,

40:52.749 --> 40:54.729
that's 272.

40:56.189 --> 40:57.568
Are they defrosted?

40:58.269 --> 41:03.249
- Your Excellency, they are.
- I thought you won't help.

41:03.628 --> 41:07.729
Wash out the blood
with the water and vinegar.

41:08.588 --> 41:12.008
May I say no, Your Excellency?

41:13.709 --> 41:15.289
Only if

41:17.628 --> 41:19.088
you dare to.

41:22.548 --> 41:23.968
I dare not.

41:26.028 --> 41:28.805
- Fine.
- Am I doing fine?

41:28.829 --> 41:31.809
- Should I pluck the hair?
- What do you think?

41:36.909 --> 41:38.088
Here.

41:51.028 --> 41:52.028
Wine.

41:59.948 --> 42:01.128
It should be fine.

42:05.508 --> 42:06.508
Here.

42:11.909 --> 42:15.289
It's going to be a long night.
It smells nice but it's not ready.

42:15.669 --> 42:17.648
Sheng, soybean paste.

42:18.109 --> 42:19.209
Thank you.

42:27.269 --> 42:29.689
It smells great.

42:42.829 --> 42:45.409
- But I can't eat it.
- Raw garlic?

42:46.189 --> 42:47.804
- It's nice.
- Don't talk to me.

42:48.508 --> 42:49.660
Does it smell good?

42:50.469 --> 42:51.628
Yes.

